Class TestPlanManager

java.lang.Object

public class TestPlanManager extends Object
This class manages the functions performed on and by a test plan

  • Method Details

    • loadTestPlans

      public void loadTestPlans(File fileName)
      This class loads all the test plans and their respective test cases from a file by calling the TestPlanReader class's methods and adds them to the list of test plans if it does not already exist in the list. The current test plan is then set to failingTestList.
      Parameters:
      fileName - of the file to be read from

    • saveTestPlans

      public void saveTestPlans(File fileName)
      This class saves all the test plans and their respective test cases to the given file by calling the TestPlanWriter class's methods. isChanged is updated to false.
      Parameters:
      fileName - of the file to be saved

    • isChanged

      public boolean isChanged()
      Updates the isChanged variable based on the updates made to the test plan
      Returns:
      true if the test plan has had changes made

    • addTestPlan

      public void addTestPlan(String planName)
      Adds a testPlan with the given name to the list of test plans and updates the current test plane to the test plan that was just added
      Parameters:
      planName - for the test plan to be added
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - with the message "Invalid name." if the test plans name is a duplicate of a plan that already exists or if it is "Failing Tests"

    • getTestPlanNames

      public String[] getTestPlanNames()
      Returns an array of the names of the test plans with the failing ones at the top
      Returns:
      an array of Strings

    • setCurrentTestPlan

      public void setCurrentTestPlan(String planName)
      Sets the current test plan to the AbstractTestPlan with the given name. If a test plan with the given name is not found, the currentTestPlan is set to feilingTestList
      Parameters:
      planName - to change the test plan name into

    • getCurrentTestPlan

      public AbstractTestPlan getCurrentTestPlan()
      Returns the current test plan
      Returns:
      the current test plan

    • editTestPlan

      public void editTestPlan(String planName)
      This method allows for the editing of the name of a test plan and updates isChanged to true.
      Parameters:
      planName - to change into
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if the currentTestPlan is an FailingTestList, if the name is "Failing Tests", or if the name is a duplicate.

    • removeTestPlan

      public void removeTestPlan()
      This method deletes the current test plan and updates isChanged to true if the test plan was deleted
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - with the message "The Failing Tests list may not be deleted." if the currentTestPlan is set to failingTestList
